# WP Stack (WordPress + MariaDB on K8s)

Deploys WordPress + MariaDB to Kubernetes (tested on Minikube on Amazon Linux EC2).  
Includes Helm chart for app, PVCs, and optional Ingress. Monitoring via `kube-prometheus-stack` + Grafana.

## Prerequisites
- Kubernetes cluster (e.g. Minikube)
- `kubectl`, `helm` installed
- Images in ECR:
  - WordPress: `992382545251.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress-amiel:latest`
  - MariaDB:   `992382545251.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/mariadb-amiel:10.6.4-focal`
- (Optional) Ingress-NGINX Controller

## Install

```bash
cd wp-stack

# install/upgrade
helm upgrade --install wp .

# wait until Ready
kubectl get pods -w   # Ctrl+C when wordpress pods are 1/1 and mariadb-0 is 1/1

